The paper introduces a new measure of discrepancy in strategic games, which is related to game theory (cs.GT) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The analysis of various games involves computational and algorithmic aspects, which could fall under data structures (cs.DS) and machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper discusses the impact of players' decisions on society as a whole, which could be relevant to social and information networks (cs.SI).
